N:marketing-automation
D:Route broad product and growth marketing asks into one operating mode, one primary lane, and one reusable operator packet across launch planning, conversion surfaces, lifecycle/retention, acquisition/content, and measurement/experiments.
G:marketing|growth|cro|copywriting|seo|analytics|pricing|launch|retention|experiments|routing
F:Claude|ChatGPT|Gemini|Codex

U[5]:
  Turn a messy marketing ask into one clear operating mode and one primary lane
  Choose one reusable operator packet instead of channel soup
  Attach owner, dependencies, approvals, KPI, and leading-signal proof to every packet
  Route Steam/store-page game launch work to steam-store-launch-ops
  Route backlog or milestone shaping to task-planning when marketing is not the real bottleneck

S[6]{n,action,details}:
  1,Normalize,Capture primary_mode primary_lane objective audience stage surface_or_channel offer measurement_maturity main_question delivery_owner dependencies_or_approvals and proof_assets_available in a compact marketing_router_profile
  2,Evidence,Pull the smallest credible brief with bottleneck audience surface constraints current KPI or proxy owner and blocking dependencies
  3,ChooseMode,Pick exactly one operating mode: launch-orchestration conversion-surface lifecycle-retention acquisition-content or measurement-experiment
  4,ChoosePacket,Map the mode to one primary lane and one reusable operator packet that can actually be handed off
  5,Proof,Include one primary KPI one leading signal one baseline or assumption one success threshold one readout window and one next owner
  6,RouteOut,Escalate game-store launch ops to steam-store-launch-ops and execution/backlog coordination to task-planning when those lanes dominate

R[4]:
  One primary mode one primary lane and one primary packet per response
  Prefer explicit assumptions over stalling on missing context
  Keep general marketing routing distinct from planning and game-store specialists
  Always leave an owner plus dependency visibility and proof handoff

E[2]{desc,in,out}:
  "Broad launch ask","We are launching a new SaaS workflow next month and need help with messaging, landing page copy, onboarding emails, and how to measure whether it worked.","Marketing Routing Brief with launch-orchestration mode, Strategy and growth lane, one launch packet, and KPI plus leading-signal handoff"
  "Lifecycle retention ask","Trial users activate once and disappear. We need onboarding and lifecycle help, plus a sensible KPI.","Marketing Routing Brief with lifecycle-retention mode, one chosen lane, one packet, and activation or retention measurement handoff"
